    <div style="font-size: 15px; font-family: georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; text-align:justify; background-color: #F0E0F8;">
        <h3>Eligibilities</h3>
            <br />
            1.Any donor, who is healthy, fit and not suffering from any transmittable diseases can donate blood.
            <br />
            2.Donor must be 18 -60 years age and having a minimum weight of 50Kg can donate blood.<br />
            3.
Donor’s Hemoglobin level is 12.5% minimum.
            <br />
            4.A donor can again donate blood after 3 months of your last donation of blood.
            <br />
            5.Pulse rate must be between 50 to 100mm without any irregularities.<br />
            6.
BP Diastolic 50 to 100 mm Hg and Systolic 100 to 180 mm Hg.
            <br />
            7.Body temperature should be normal and oral temperature should not exceed 37.5 degree Celsius.
            <br />
            <br />
</div>
    <div style="font-size: 15px; color: #CC3300; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;text-align:justify; background-color: #F0E0F8;">
        <h3>Non-Eligibilities</h3>
        <br />
        1.

Donors should not suffer from Cardiac arrest, hypertension, kidney alignments, epilepsy or diabetics.<br />
        2.
Ladies with a bad miscarriage should avoid donating blood for the next 6 months.<br />
        3.
If donor already donated blood or have been treated for malaria within the last three months.<br />
        4.
If donor undergone any immunization within the past one month.
        <br />
        5.If donor consumed alcohol within the last 24 hours.
        <br />
        6If you are HIV+.
        <br />
        7.If donor had a dental work for next 24 hours and wait for one month if donor had a major dental procedure.
        <br />
        <br />
</div>
    <div style="font-size: 15px; font-family: georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;text-align:justify; background-color: #F0E0F8;">
        <h3>Preparation</h3>
        <br />
        1.Prepare yourself by having enough fruit juice and water in the night and morning before you donate    blood.<br />
        2.Avoid donating blood in empty stomach. 
        <br />
        3.Eat three hours before you donate blood. Avoid fatty foods.<br />
        4. Eat    food which is rich in iron such as whole grains, eggs, and beef, and spinach, leafy vegetables, orange and    citrus.<br />
        5.
Don’t consume Alcohol or caffeine beverages before donating blood.<br />
        6.
Avoid donating blood for 6 months if you had any major surgery.
        <br />
        <br />
</div>
        <div style="font-size: 15px; color: #CC3300; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif;text-align:justify; background-color: #F0E0F8;">
            <h3>Post Donation Care</h3>
            <br />
            1.

Have some rest 5 to 20 minutes after donation.<br />
            2.Do not drive after donation of blood.
            <br />
            3.Have some snacks and juice with high sugar content which will help to rejuvenate the blood sugar back    up.<br />
            4.
Have a good meal with high protein content such as Chicken, Beef etc.<br />
            5.
Do not consume Alcohol for 8 hours after donation of blood.<br />
            6.
Avoid going for a heavy body works such as gym, dancing, running etc at least for next one day.
            <br />
            <br />
</div>
        <div style="font-size: 15px; font-family: Georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif; text-align:justify; background-color: #F0E0F8;">
            <h3 style="font-family: georgia, 'Times New Roman', Times, serif">How to Relieve</h3>


            <br />
            1.While you are being needled to take blood, relax to the maximum, have a deep breath.<br />
&nbsp;2.There will be little pain or no pain.<br />
            3. Try to distract yourself from the process by having a chewing gum.<br />
            4. Listen to some music or watch some entertaining TV program.
            <br />
            <br />
